Case Based, Theory. 

Case-based reasoning is the main focus of the paper, as the authors describe the development and implementation of Kritik, a case-based design system. The paper also discusses the integration of case-based and model-based reasoning, which is a theoretical aspect of AI. The authors emphasize the importance of grounding the computational process of case-based reasoning in the SBF content theory of device comprehension, which is a theoretical framework for understanding how devices work.
